Provision a new Rascal host using the default infrastructure provider (currently Hetzner Cloud).

Usage:
  rascal provision [flags]

Examples:
rascal provision --token "$HCLOUD_TOKEN"
rascal provision --name rascal-prod --server-type cax21

Flags:
      --apply-firewall          create/update and attach a basic firewall (22,80,443) (default true)
      --firewall-name string    Hetzner firewall resource name (default "rascal-fw")
  -h, --help                    help for provision
      --image string            Hetzner image (default "ubuntu-24.04")
      --location string         Hetzner location (default "fsn1")
      --name string             server name
      --server-type string      Hetzner server type (default "cx23")
      --ssh-key-name string     Hetzner SSH key resource name (default "rascal")
      --ssh-public-key string   local SSH public key path (default "~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub")
      --timeout duration        provision timeout (default 8m0s)
      --token string            Hetzner Cloud token (or HCLOUD_TOKEN)

Global Flags:
      --api-token string         orchestrator API token
      --client-ssh-host string   SSH target host for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-key string    SSH private key path for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-port int      SSH target port for API transport=ssh/auto
      --client-ssh-user string   SSH target user for API transport=ssh/auto
      --config string            config file path (default "$HOME/.rascal/config.toml")
      --default-repo string      default repository in OWNER/REPO form
      --env-file string          env file path (fallback: ./.rascal.env if present)
      --no-color                 disable ANSI color/style output (also set by NO_COLOR)
      --output string            output format: table|json|toml (default "table")
  -q, --quiet                    reduce non-essential output
      --server-url string        orchestrator URL
      --transport string         API transport: auto|http|ssh
